content: Great simulator for learning to fly and a little addicting.  Best on a tablet as on my Samsung S5 the controls are too small to accurately use.  Would LOVE the ability to use my FrSky Taranis with this for more realistic control.

If your mobile device has the graphics horsepower to run this app, then this is the way to practice flying your quad! Selectable camera views allow you to pilot the simulated quad as if you are standing on the ground, or via FPV views from a fixed or gimbal-mounted camera. The response of the simulated quad is exceptionally realistic, as are the results of pilot errors, right down to broken props or a disabled quad after a high-speed crash. The environments are very well-done, and are carefully crafted to provide many different flight challenges. I bought the full version after playing with the free version for five minutes! This app runs exceptionally well on my Nvidia Shield, my HP Slate 7 Extreme, my Asus Memo Pad 10 FHD, my Samsung S4 Zoom, and my no-name quad-core AllWinner Android TV dongle.
How to I bind the controls to my moga android controller.
replyContent: Connect your Controller to the device (Refer to device Manufacturer's manual). Go to settings page of our simulator. Click Controller Settings Button, then Enable Controller Button. Move the Controller analog sticks. The controller graphics on the screen should respond. You can click controller mapping if the sticks are not properly mapped. Thanks
